verbose_text: As expected, miR-342-3p overexpression notably suppressed the expression of TGF-beta1, FN, C-IV, and enhanced PTEN expression at both the mRNA and protein level (XREF_FIG); however, SOX6 overexpression partly impaired the miR-342-3p-induced suppression of renal interstitial fibrosis, as the levels of the above mentioned biomarkers increased following SOX6 overexpression.
